# ── Job Search Copilot — .gitignore ────────────────────────────────────────
# Goal: version-control the TOOL (jobsdb.py, schema.sql, the *.md skill files,
# tests) while keeping every candidate's PERSONAL DATA out of git. This matches
# the handoff model in HOW_TO_USE.md — share the folder, not the pipeline.

# ── Credentials / session artifacts (never commit) ──
# Leftover ATS scraping cookie jars contain live session tokens.
cookies.txt
*.cookies
cookies/

# ── The database (single source of truth = personal pipeline data) ──
# Recreated from schema.sql via `python jobsdb.py init`. schema.sql IS tracked.
jobs.db
jobs.db.bak*
*.db
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3
# WAL/SHM sidecars if SQLite ever runs in WAL mode
*.db-wal
*.db-shm

# ── Candidate deliverables & personal documents ──
# Tailored resumes, cover letters, and the base resume are personal.
candidates/
*.docx

# ── Generated outputs (reproducible from the DB) ──
exports/

# ── Scan audit trail (dated, personal job-search history) ──
# Kept locally as the audit trail, but it's one candidate's data — not shared.
job_scans/
# discover.py company batches — same deal (dated, local). NOTE: companies_seed/ is the
# opposite — it's the shared, checked-in reset-proof company baseline, so it is NOT ignored.
company_scans/

# ── Stray scratch dumps in the repo ROOT (safety net) ──
# Discovery subagents sometimes curl raw ATS JSON/HTML to disk while verifying
# postings and don't always clean up. The leading "/" anchors these to the root
# ONLY — sanctioned homes (job_scans/, exports/) and all tracked source
# (*.py, *.md, *.sql, .gitignore) live elsewhere and are unaffected.
# If you ever add a real root-level .json/.html to track, `git add -f <file>`.
/*.json
/*.html

# ── Python ──
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
*.egg-info/
.pytest_cache/
.venv/
venv/
env/

# ── OS / editor cruft ──
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.vscode/
.idea/
*.swp
